      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's great to hear that the infection has resolved on its own, but it's recommended to complete the full 10-day course of antibiotics even if symptoms have improved. Stopping early can lead to antibiotic resistance, where the infection bacteria become more resilient and may develop immunity to the medication. Additionally, antibiotics don't just treat the infection, but also any other underlying bacterial factors that may be contributing to it.",
